Quote: [Hdg] Accusations fly about bad setting and arbitrary scaling in last year's Bursary exams... The New Zealand Qualifications Authority, which commissioned the paper, had to scale the marks more than ever before to get a median mark of 55 per cent, although scaling couldn't help those students who were so distressed that they simply walked out without attempting the questions.
